content.description:
Sit start left hand on a good side pull and right on a low sharp flake.

Make a hard sequence of moves to gain good hold for the left and then make a big move to improving holds on the slab.  Finish up the slab with little trouble.

climbs.name: Truth Crushed to Earth Will Rise Again

content.description:
Sit start with hands on the large left facing side pull.   Pull on and via a good crimp for the right gain another good left side pull.   From here make the crux span up to a sharp rail.

With the rail at hand make two more big moves and then pull onto the slab above and finish carefully up the slab.
content.location: Left side of the East face

content.description: Sit start on the small glassy sidepull features  down and left from where "Truth Crushed to Earth..." starts. Pull onto the wall and make a hard first move into the V4, match the undercling sidepull and continue traversing rightwards on small slightly crusty crimps, gastons and slopers. After a series of long and strenuous moves, make your way past Pleiadas and continue up and right into the top out of "Vinland".
content.protection: Atleast 3 pads and a spotter or two.
content.location: Odin's Cave. This line traverses the entire wall left to right.

content.description:
Climb the steep slabby face via an obvious rounded right facing feature two thirds of the way up.

Tall, technical and tenuous - not the ideal combo!!
content.protection: Lots of pads and a spotter or two
content.location: Right side of the cave entrance

content.description:
The sharp fin of rock on the east side of the cave is climbed via small sharp crimps and big finishing moves.

Surprisingly fun.
content.location: right side of the cave mid way in

content.description:
Sit start with hands on good incuts.

Make two hard moves to gain a left facing slanting crimp and with that at hand move up left and then into the scoop for an easier finish.

After a tricky start climb up the wall using good but small side pulls and features.   Avoid using any help from the left and the large boulder / edge.

Tall but it gets easier up high.
content.location: Right side of the cave entrance
